1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:03,070
Gon: Kite is still alive.

2
00:00:03,103 --> 00:00:04,071
( Killua gasps )

3
00:00:04,104 --> 00:00:06,273
Gon: He would never be beaten,

4
00:00:06,306 --> 00:00:08,241
not by something like that.

5
00:00:08,275 --> 00:00:13,147
So now we get strong,
and we find him.

6
00:00:14,982 --> 00:00:16,917
We’re gonna go save kite.

7
00:00:17,618 --> 00:00:18,586
♪

8
00:00:18,619 --> 00:00:20,621
( Singing in Japanese )

9
00:01:01,995 --> 00:01:03,997
♪

10
00:01:08,969 --> 00:01:12,005
Narrator: Gon and killua
have vowed to save kite,

11
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:15,075
but before
they can return to the ngl,

12
00:01:15,108 --> 00:01:17,844
they must fulfill
the one condition set

13
00:01:17,878 --> 00:01:21,782
by chairman netero, the leader
of the extermination team.

14
00:01:23,183 --> 00:01:24,985
Gon: What are those, killua?

15
00:01:25,018 --> 00:01:26,853
Killua: They’re shogi tiles.

16
00:01:26,887 --> 00:01:29,590
You take a piece of marked wood
and split it.

17
00:01:29,623 --> 00:01:31,992
Then you give each half
to a different person.

18
00:01:32,025 --> 00:01:34,794
You can use it
as proof of identity

19
00:01:34,828 --> 00:01:36,396
or to verify a document.

20
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,667
Netero: We have already
placed two assassins

21
00:01:40,701 --> 00:01:42,002
in the nearest city.

22
00:01:45,639 --> 00:01:47,007
Killua: In this case,

23
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:50,410
each of the two assassins
have the other halves.

24
00:01:51,912 --> 00:01:54,815
We’ll beat ’em
and take their pieces.

25
00:02:02,656 --> 00:02:04,658
( Overlapping chatter )

26
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,961
It’s been erased.

27
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:10,931
That means someone
checked the board.

28
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:11,965
( Gon grunts )

29
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:17,571
♪

30
00:02:17,604 --> 00:02:20,907
Woman: You must be
killua and gon.

31
00:02:22,209 --> 00:02:25,279
It’s nice to meet you.

32
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:27,281
My name...

33
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:28,749
Is palm.

34
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,985
It’s a pleasure.

35
00:02:33,387 --> 00:02:35,956
Ah, don’t be like that.

36
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:38,291
There’s no reason to be nervous.

37
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:41,962
I imagine the chairman didn’t
tell you very much, did he?

38
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:44,130
Allow me to explain.

39
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:47,134
Let’s sit down
and have some tea.

40
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,168
( Boys grunt )

41
00:02:50,204 --> 00:02:54,108
Palm: I am knov’s pupil,
you see.

42
00:02:54,141 --> 00:02:57,645
He told me I would
only get in his way,

43
00:02:57,678 --> 00:03:00,714
but I insisted
on accompanying him.

44
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:02,115
Gon: Who’s that?

45
00:03:02,149 --> 00:03:03,283
Killua: Don’t know.

46
00:03:03,317 --> 00:03:05,286
One of the guys
with chairman netero?

47
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:07,755
Palm: Yes,
the one in a black suit.

48
00:03:07,788 --> 00:03:10,591
My teacher is a wonderful man,

49
00:03:10,624 --> 00:03:14,595
cool and intelligent
and composed.

50
00:03:14,628 --> 00:03:18,232
Oh! Cool and composed
mean the same thing.

51
00:03:18,265 --> 00:03:20,734
I only admire him. That’s all.

52
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:23,837
There’s nothing romantic
or anything.

53
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:27,942
Except i’m not certain
of that either.

54
00:03:27,975 --> 00:03:29,877
( Nervous laugh )

55
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:32,346
I mean, respect is
a considerable factor

56
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:35,249
when it comes
to falling in love, after all.

57
00:03:35,282 --> 00:03:38,952
( Gasps ) And my teacher knows
nothing about this, of course.

58
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:42,957
I have never said a word
to him, and I never will.

59
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:45,326
( Slurping )

60
00:03:45,359 --> 00:03:47,328
( Boys groaning )

61
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:49,330
( Palm sighs )

62
00:03:49,363 --> 00:03:51,265
Though in matters of the heart,

63
00:03:51,298 --> 00:03:53,333
you can never
really say for certain.

64
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:56,070
Love is a spontaneous thing.

65
00:03:56,103 --> 00:03:58,872
That goes without saying.
Don’t you agree?

66
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,908
Killua: Uh, can I interrupt?

67
00:04:00,941 --> 00:04:02,976
Aren’t we supposed to fight you?

68
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:05,045
Palm: Huh? Oh, dear, yes.

69
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:06,880
I apologize.

70
00:04:06,914 --> 00:04:10,818
The chairman and my teacher
said I couldn’t accompany them,

71
00:04:10,851 --> 00:04:13,987
which is quite unfortunate,
if you ask me.

72
00:04:14,021 --> 00:04:17,992
But I insisted on going
with them. I had to.

73
00:04:18,025 --> 00:04:20,628
It feels like I spent a lifetime

74
00:04:20,661 --> 00:04:22,997
trying to prove
my determination to them,

75
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:25,766
but they finally conceded,
with a stipulation.

76
00:04:25,799 --> 00:04:27,768
- ( Laughs )
- Killua: Not what I asked.

77
00:04:27,801 --> 00:04:29,803
Palm: I know
what you’re thinking.

78
00:04:29,837 --> 00:04:33,007
My teacher seems so cold,
but he’s actually kind.

79
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,642
That’s easier to see

80
00:04:34,675 --> 00:04:37,311
once you’ve spent
as much time with him as I have.

81
00:04:37,344 --> 00:04:39,313
Ah! Of course,
by "spending time with him,"

82
00:04:39,346 --> 00:04:41,181
I don’t mean that he and I are--

83
00:04:41,215 --> 00:04:43,617
killua: Agh!
What is the condition?!

84
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:48,021
Palm: You have to take down
knuckle and shoot.

85
00:04:48,055 --> 00:04:51,191
It’s unthinkable, really.

86
00:04:51,225 --> 00:04:54,261
How dare those vulgar,
rude, barbaric brats

87
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:57,631
go to the ngl before me?

88
00:04:57,664 --> 00:05:00,300
I simply cannot allow it.

89
00:05:00,334 --> 00:05:02,136
Gon: Whoa!
Hey, miss palm, please,

90
00:05:02,169 --> 00:05:04,071
you’ve gotta stop
using your hatsu!

91
00:05:04,104 --> 00:05:05,739
( Wiping )

92
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:08,074
So she’s an enhancer like me.

93
00:05:08,108 --> 00:05:09,977
I don’t like this.

94
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:11,879
Killua: Hold on.
"Knuckle and shoot"?

95
00:05:11,912 --> 00:05:13,781
So you’re not here to fight us?

96
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,282
- Palm: That’s right.
- ( Both gasp )

97
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:19,085
Palm: After all, I am not
the one who’s been assigned

98
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:22,789
to defeating knuckle and shoot.
That job belongs to you.

99
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:23,991
( Both grunt )

100
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:26,026
Palm: You see, knuckle and shoot

101
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:27,794
are students of Mr. Morel.

102
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:29,797
♪

103
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:33,300
They, too, received a condition.

104
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:36,203
Unfortunately,
I don’t know what it was,

105
00:05:36,236 --> 00:05:39,940
but I know this.
Whether it’s us or them,

106
00:05:39,973 --> 00:05:42,209
only one group will be allowed.

107
00:05:42,242 --> 00:05:45,812
We only have one month’s time.

108
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:48,282
Hunter: Okay. We were told

109
00:05:48,315 --> 00:05:51,585
to keep these tiles
in our possession for a month,

110
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:53,620
so you can bet
that in that time

111
00:05:53,654 --> 00:05:56,824
someone’s gonna come for them.

112
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:03,964
So, knuckle, what do we do?

113
00:06:03,997 --> 00:06:07,868
Knuckle: Strike first,
and we win.

114
00:06:07,901 --> 00:06:10,537
We’ll find ’em, and...

115
00:06:10,571 --> 00:06:11,772
We’ll kill ’em!

116
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:14,074
♪

117
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:16,676
( Amplified )
My name is knuckle bine,

118
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:19,079
and i’m a beast hunter!

119
00:06:19,112 --> 00:06:23,283
Extermination team candidates,
I challenge you to a duel!

120
00:06:23,317 --> 00:06:26,821
Midnight tonight,
and don’t be late!

121
00:06:26,854 --> 00:06:28,956
Fight me fair and square!

122
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:31,692
I won’t try to hide or run away!

123
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:33,961
I won’t bring weapons or allies!

124
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:36,697
It’ll just be me and me alone!

125
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,233
So come and fight me, okay?!

126
00:06:39,266 --> 00:06:40,601
Man: Where?

127
00:06:40,634 --> 00:06:42,169
Man #2: What location?

128
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:45,205
Man #3: You have to to tell them
where to find you.

129
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:47,108
Knuckle: Bring it on! Hear me?!

130
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:50,010
A man knows never
to turn his back on an enemy!

131
00:06:50,043 --> 00:06:52,812
I’m prepared to follow you
to the ends of the earth!

132
00:06:52,846 --> 00:06:54,815
You won’t get away from me!

133
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:57,617
Killua: I wouldn’t go,
even if he said where.

134
00:06:57,651 --> 00:07:00,120
He’s just a decoy.

135
00:07:00,153 --> 00:07:02,255
His partner’s
probably hiding somewhere.

136
00:07:02,289 --> 00:07:04,191
You know,
i’m even willing to bet

137
00:07:04,224 --> 00:07:06,793
that they’re watching to see
if anyone reacts suspiciously

138
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:08,562
before they make a move,

139
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:11,565
and according to palm,
they don’t even know our names,

140
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:13,767
- so we’re in the clear.
- Gon: Mm-hmm.

141
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:17,003
Killua: They were just trying
to lure us out somehow.

142
00:07:17,037 --> 00:07:19,873
Only an idiot
would pull a stunt like that.

143
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:22,309
Gon: What did the guy look like?
Was he powerful?

144
00:07:22,342 --> 00:07:24,277
Killua: He’s tough.

145
00:07:27,314 --> 00:07:29,750
Gon: What’s it gonna take
to defeat him?

146
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:31,885
Killua: Your guess
is as good as mine.

147
00:07:31,919 --> 00:07:34,155
One of the hunters
with the chairman

148
00:07:34,188 --> 00:07:37,892
said that in a battle
nothing is certain.

149
00:07:37,925 --> 00:07:40,661
Also according to that guy,

150
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:44,231
i’m not qualified to judge
if a fight can be won.

151
00:07:44,264 --> 00:07:46,099
But I disagree.

152
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,002
If you want to survive,

153
00:07:48,035 --> 00:07:50,738
you have to increase
your odds of victory.

154
00:07:50,771 --> 00:07:52,006
Gauging
the strength differential

155
00:07:52,039 --> 00:07:54,275
between you
and your opponent is key.

156
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:55,309
( Slurps )

157
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:59,179
If you’re fighting someone
you could only beat

158
00:07:59,213 --> 00:08:02,049
once or twice out of
a hundred tries, don’t bother.

159
00:08:02,082 --> 00:08:04,885
( Gon gasps )

160
00:08:04,918 --> 00:08:07,154
Killua: You want
50-50 at least...

161
00:08:08,622 --> 00:08:11,291
70% or better
if it’s at all possible.

162
00:08:11,325 --> 00:08:13,227
And for us
to get to that point,

163
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:15,562
there are still two things
we have to do.

164
00:08:15,596 --> 00:08:18,732
We need to work
on all our fundamental skills

165
00:08:18,765 --> 00:08:20,700
and learn about
our opponents’ abilities.

166
00:08:20,734 --> 00:08:21,902
( Gon grunts )

167
00:08:21,935 --> 00:08:24,604
Killua: If we find out
what they are,

168
00:08:24,638 --> 00:08:27,808
we can plan ahead just like
we did against genthru.

169
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:29,176
Gon: Hmm.

170
00:08:29,209 --> 00:08:31,978
Half of me agrees with you,
and half doesn’t.

171
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:33,847
Killua: What does that mean?

172
00:08:33,881 --> 00:08:36,951
Gon: I agree that we should
work on our fundamentals.

173
00:08:36,984 --> 00:08:39,053
I just don’t agree
we need to know

174
00:08:39,086 --> 00:08:40,588
exactly what
their abilities are.

175
00:08:40,621 --> 00:08:43,090
Killua: Really?
Why the hell not?

176
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:45,225
Come on!
Why add to all the risks

177
00:08:45,259 --> 00:08:46,994
without any real benefits?

178
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:49,096
Gon: I know,
but once we’re inside,

179
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:51,598
that is what we’re
going to be facing.

180
00:08:51,632 --> 00:08:53,000
( Killua gasps )

181
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:55,669
Gon: Our goal isn’t
to defeat knuckle and shoot.

182
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,070
It’s to get stronger,

183
00:08:57,104 --> 00:09:00,107
strong enough to go back
to the ngl and rescue kite.

184
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:02,075
♪

185
00:09:04,311 --> 00:09:07,581
I mean, we’ve gotta be powerful
enough to beat enemies

186
00:09:07,614 --> 00:09:10,650
we don’t know anything about
at a moment’s notice.

187
00:09:10,684 --> 00:09:14,221
If we always need to plan ahead,
then what’s the point?

188
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:15,789
Killua: That’s true,

189
00:09:15,822 --> 00:09:18,558
but we’ve still gotta beat
these guys first.

190
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:23,897
After all, we only have a month
to get this done, remember?

191
00:09:23,931 --> 00:09:25,166
Gon: That’s too long.

192
00:09:25,199 --> 00:09:26,167
Killua: Eh?

193
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,768
Gon: Seven days.

194
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:30,704
In one week, we’ll get
strong enough to go back!

195
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:31,972
Killua: Ah? Bu--

196
00:09:32,005 --> 00:09:34,174
- ( gon yelps )
- Bisky: Are you an idiot?!

197
00:09:35,809 --> 00:09:36,977
( Killua gasps )

198
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:37,978
Gon: Huh?!

199
00:09:38,011 --> 00:09:39,246
Boys: Biscuit!

200
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,647
Bisky: Mm-hmm.

201
00:09:40,681 --> 00:09:42,583
Boys: Why are you here?

202
00:09:42,616 --> 00:09:44,585
Palm: Because I
invited her to come.

203
00:09:44,618 --> 00:09:47,154
Boys: You two know each other?

204
00:09:47,187 --> 00:09:50,824
Palm: No. I just did
a little research on you.

205
00:09:50,858 --> 00:09:53,294
Gon: Okay, but we
only know her from--

206
00:09:53,327 --> 00:09:55,162
- ( palm laughs )
- ( Boys gasp )

207
00:09:55,195 --> 00:09:58,899
Palm: Once I used my ability,
it was really quite simple.

208
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:02,903
There’s no time left to spare,
so let’s begin.

209
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:07,073
We must plot to kill
Mr. Morel’s disciples.

210
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:08,175
Boys: No, thanks.

211
00:10:13,914 --> 00:10:15,883
Bisky: Now let’s get started.

212
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:16,884
Boys: Osu!

213
00:10:16,917 --> 00:10:18,752
( Gon gasps ) Ohh!

214
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:20,620
That hurt! What was that for?

215
00:10:20,654 --> 00:10:22,156
Bisky: I’m picking up
where I left off.

216
00:10:22,189 --> 00:10:23,791
What are you, an idiot?

217
00:10:23,824 --> 00:10:27,928
That old man is notorious
for being very unreasonable.

218
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:30,697
( Netero laughs )

219
00:10:30,731 --> 00:10:33,234
Bisky: If he tells you
to do something in only a month,

220
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,770
then it will probably
take you at least a full year,

221
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:37,304
and that’s if you’re lucky.

222
00:10:37,337 --> 00:10:39,706
There’s no way you’ll
defeat them in just a week.

223
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:41,075
Gon: But you don’t understand!

224
00:10:41,108 --> 00:10:43,611
We have to get back there
as soon as possible

225
00:10:43,644 --> 00:10:44,845
so we can save kite!

226
00:10:44,878 --> 00:10:46,613
Bisky: Wait.
What are you talking about?

227
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:48,616
♪

228
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:57,191
Neferpitou:
That was so much fun.

229
00:10:57,224 --> 00:11:00,694
It felt like a dream.

230
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:08,201
I’d love to do it again...

231
00:11:10,037 --> 00:11:11,872
With you.

232
00:11:12,973 --> 00:11:15,275
Bisky: I see.

233
00:11:15,309 --> 00:11:19,079
Well, that’s all the more reason
you can’t rush your training.

234
00:11:19,112 --> 00:11:20,647
( Gon groans )

235
00:11:20,681 --> 00:11:23,083
Bisky: What if you make
those same mistakes again?

236
00:11:23,116 --> 00:11:24,618
Killua: At her age,

237
00:11:24,651 --> 00:11:27,287
no wonder she’s a pro
at chewing people out.

238
00:11:27,321 --> 00:11:29,290
Bisky: Do you understand?

239
00:11:29,323 --> 00:11:31,125
Gon: Osu.

240
00:11:31,158 --> 00:11:33,193
Bisky: Let’s start
your training, then.

241
00:11:35,963 --> 00:11:38,766
Show me ren.

242
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:41,001
♪

243
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:45,005
All right, now. You are to
maintain that for three hours.

244
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:46,606
( Both gasp )

245
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:49,610
Gon: Killua,
how long can you go?

246
00:11:49,643 --> 00:11:51,011
Killua: On a really good day,

247
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,213
I can do
just about 55 minutes Max.

248
00:11:53,247 --> 00:11:56,117
Bisky: Do that, and then we can
move on to the next step.

249
00:11:56,149 --> 00:11:59,319
Train like your lives
depend on it.

250
00:11:59,353 --> 00:12:01,055
( Laughs )

251
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:06,260
( Gon panting )

252
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:15,069
( Killua groans )

253
00:12:15,102 --> 00:12:18,839
Bisky: Oh, come on.
You didn’t even last an hour.

254
00:12:18,872 --> 00:12:20,674
Okay, now keep going!

255
00:12:26,713 --> 00:12:29,049
They say it should take
about a month

256
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:31,751
to prolong your ren
by a mere ten minutes.

257
00:12:31,785 --> 00:12:34,288
That means we can’t spare
any time for sleep.

258
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,228
( Dog whimpers )

259
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:43,096
Knuckle: Damn them.

260
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:46,767
Those damn bastards
didn’t even show up!

261
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,802
You cowards deserve to die!

262
00:12:48,836 --> 00:12:50,604
( Dog barking )

263
00:12:56,043 --> 00:12:58,946
( Groans )
Okay, you’ve got a collar,

264
00:12:58,979 --> 00:13:00,781
so where the hell’s your owner?

265
00:13:00,814 --> 00:13:02,883
You gotta pick up
after your dogs.

266
00:13:02,916 --> 00:13:04,851
Keep our parks clean, damn it.

267
00:13:05,886 --> 00:13:06,854
Bisky: All right!

268
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:08,055
That’s enough for today.

269
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:12,659
Tomorrow begins in 30 minutes.

270
00:13:12,693 --> 00:13:16,063
( Boys snoring )

271
00:13:16,096 --> 00:13:18,098
Bisky: And from the looks of it,

272
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:21,034
now would be the perfect time
to use my ability.

273
00:13:21,068 --> 00:13:22,303
Hmm.

274
00:13:25,939 --> 00:13:27,941
♪

275
00:13:37,818 --> 00:13:40,788
Well, you’re up, cookie. Go on!

276
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:44,057
( Piano playing )

277
00:13:46,260 --> 00:13:50,998
Magical spa services
peachy relief--piano massage!

278
00:13:52,266 --> 00:13:53,601
( Gon sighs )

279
00:13:53,634 --> 00:13:55,769
( Bisky sighs )

280
00:13:55,802 --> 00:13:57,604
- Palm: Excuse me.
- Bisky: Huh?

281
00:13:57,638 --> 00:14:00,741
Palm: I do hope
i’m not rude for saying this,

282
00:14:00,774 --> 00:14:03,610
but i’ll let you choose
how to train them.

283
00:14:03,644 --> 00:14:07,148
My ability selected you
as the answer I seek, after all.

284
00:14:07,181 --> 00:14:11,285
However, if after a month,
we determine

285
00:14:11,318 --> 00:14:14,955
it would be impossible for them
to defeat morel’s pupils,

286
00:14:14,988 --> 00:14:20,560
I sincerely doubt that I would
be able to restrain myself.

287
00:14:20,594 --> 00:14:26,200
I must go to the ngl.
I want to go right now, in fact.

288
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:29,803
If i’m forced to wait
and wait and wait and wait

289
00:14:29,837 --> 00:14:31,772
and then I don’t get to go...

290
00:14:31,805 --> 00:14:35,976
Then i--i may end up
killing you all.

291
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:37,944
Bisky: Wait. Was that a threat?

292
00:14:37,978 --> 00:14:41,782
Palm: No, just a warning.
I don’t want to hurt you.

293
00:14:41,815 --> 00:14:44,851
Therefore if you don’t think
they stand a chance,

294
00:14:44,885 --> 00:14:47,588
you should give up sooner
rather than later.

295
00:14:47,621 --> 00:14:50,624
My anger won’t be
as terrible then,

296
00:14:50,657 --> 00:14:53,160
judging by my past experiences.

297
00:14:53,193 --> 00:14:56,563
Bisky: I’m really not the one
you should be telling that to.

298
00:14:56,597 --> 00:14:58,999
You can tell the two of them
when they’re awake, okay?

299
00:15:02,970 --> 00:15:05,206
Gon: You don’t have to worry.
We’ve got this.

300
00:15:05,239 --> 00:15:08,743
We’ll get you inside the ngl,
no matter what it takes.

301
00:15:08,775 --> 00:15:11,611
So if you have any pointers
for me or anything like that,

302
00:15:11,645 --> 00:15:12,980
you can let me know, okay?

303
00:15:13,013 --> 00:15:15,249
I’ll try hard!

304
00:15:15,282 --> 00:15:16,750
( Grunts )

305
00:15:16,783 --> 00:15:17,751
( Palm gasps )

306
00:15:17,784 --> 00:15:19,619
Bisky: That’s how he is.

307
00:15:19,653 --> 00:15:21,155
Just have faith in him.

308
00:15:21,188 --> 00:15:24,558
( Gon grunting )

309
00:15:24,591 --> 00:15:27,060
( Palm sighs )

310
00:15:27,094 --> 00:15:28,562
( Heart beats )

311
00:15:28,595 --> 00:15:32,165
- Oh, dear! Oh, gosh! Oh, no!
- Bisky: Hmm?

312
00:15:32,199 --> 00:15:34,768
Anyway, at the moment,

313
00:15:34,801 --> 00:15:37,704
i’m far more concerned
about the guys back in the ngl.

314
00:15:37,738 --> 00:15:40,874
What exactly does the chairman
plan to do for the next month?

315
00:15:40,908 --> 00:15:41,876
Hey!

316
00:15:41,909 --> 00:15:44,578
Palm: Uh, oh,

317
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:47,681
they said they were
going to "scout and whittle,"

318
00:15:47,714 --> 00:15:52,285
try to identify and chip away
the enemy strong points.

319
00:15:52,319 --> 00:15:54,755
The experts
can’t come to a consensus

320
00:15:54,788 --> 00:15:56,290
on how much time remains

321
00:15:56,323 --> 00:15:59,293
between now and
when the king is born.

322
00:15:59,326 --> 00:16:01,762
The chairman is acting
on the assumption

323
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:05,632
that the earliest it will be
is in two months.

324
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:06,700
Netero: Hmm.

325
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:09,069
This isn’t good.

326
00:16:12,673 --> 00:16:15,643
That thing looks
a lot stronger than me.

327
00:16:15,676 --> 00:16:18,712
Knov: Stronger than you,
chairman?

328
00:16:18,745 --> 00:16:20,547
Surely you jest,

329
00:16:20,581 --> 00:16:22,183
’cause if that’s the case,

330
00:16:22,216 --> 00:16:24,785
not a single hunter
in the entire world

331
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:26,520
will stand a chance against it.

332
00:16:26,553 --> 00:16:27,721
( Netero chuckles )

333
00:16:27,754 --> 00:16:29,656
It’s been more
than half a century

334
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:31,959
since I was the strongest
among nen users,

335
00:16:31,992 --> 00:16:33,760
but I do see your point.

336
00:16:33,794 --> 00:16:35,195
And although i’m flattered,

337
00:16:35,229 --> 00:16:38,065
i’m currently just about even
with the two of you.

338
00:16:38,098 --> 00:16:41,201
Knov: Then you’re more
than strong enough, chairman.

339
00:16:41,235 --> 00:16:43,838
You should be more confident.

340
00:16:43,871 --> 00:16:47,141
Netero: Even when i’m at less
than half my former glory?

341
00:16:47,174 --> 00:16:50,010
The ravages of time
come for us all.

342
00:16:50,043 --> 00:16:51,878
Knov: Always ready
with a comeback.

343
00:16:51,912 --> 00:16:53,881
Morel: But we’ve
still gotta fight ’em.

344
00:16:53,914 --> 00:16:57,918
Netero: I would prefer
to avoid that eventuality.

345
00:16:57,951 --> 00:17:01,888
A nonviolent solution
would be a much better outcome.

346
00:17:01,922 --> 00:17:06,527
Our target is the queen
and the queen alone,

347
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:08,962
but it will be quite difficult

348
00:17:08,996 --> 00:17:11,532
to slip through
his en surveillance.

349
00:17:11,565 --> 00:17:14,234
There’s no way
to avoid confrontation.

350
00:17:14,268 --> 00:17:17,905
The only question
is how we’ll manage to win.

351
00:17:17,938 --> 00:17:21,642
If you have any ideas,
i’d be glad to hear them.

352
00:17:21,675 --> 00:17:24,545
Knov: You love to tease,
don’t you?

353
00:17:24,578 --> 00:17:26,580
You already knew
what you would do

354
00:17:26,613 --> 00:17:28,982
when you chose the two of us,
didn’t you?

355
00:17:29,016 --> 00:17:31,952
♪

356
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:37,090
We go and exterminate the ants
silently one at a time.

357
00:17:48,335 --> 00:17:52,139
( Morel inhales )

358
00:18:01,014 --> 00:18:03,149
Now let’s take it slow,
all right?

359
00:18:03,183 --> 00:18:06,687
Might as well enjoy the job
while we’re at it.

360
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,922
Okay. To start with,

361
00:18:08,956 --> 00:18:12,626
let’s find exactly out how many
opponents we’re up against.

362
00:18:12,659 --> 00:18:13,660
Now go.

363
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:21,202
Neferpitou: Hmm?

364
00:18:21,235 --> 00:18:22,870
Hmm.

365
00:18:23,871 --> 00:18:27,208
So many. Something is coming...

366
00:18:27,241 --> 00:18:29,877
But they’re not alive.

367
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:32,646
Is this the enemy’s ability?

368
00:18:32,679 --> 00:18:35,081
What to do meow?

369
00:18:36,283 --> 00:18:38,018
Male: You might as well wait.

370
00:18:38,051 --> 00:18:39,686
Neferpitou: Hmm?

371
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:43,090
Male: Because I can assure you
that if they get this far,

372
00:18:43,123 --> 00:18:44,691
we will simply destroy them.

373
00:18:44,725 --> 00:18:47,094
Neferpitou: I guess
you have a point there.

374
00:18:47,127 --> 00:18:49,129
It’s possible
that they’re decoys.

375
00:18:49,163 --> 00:18:50,598
Hey, wait a sec.

376
00:18:50,631 --> 00:18:52,700
Was I just speaking out loud?

377
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,568
Male: Oh, no.

378
00:18:54,601 --> 00:18:57,304
I simply happened to know
what you were thinking about.

379
00:18:57,337 --> 00:18:59,906
Neferpitou: And who
are you, anyway?

380
00:18:59,940 --> 00:19:01,909
♪

381
00:19:03,177 --> 00:19:06,514
Male: I am one
of the queen’s royal guards.

382
00:19:06,547 --> 00:19:08,249
Call me shaiapouf.

383
00:19:08,282 --> 00:19:10,151
( Chuckles )

384
00:19:11,552 --> 00:19:12,720
( Heart beating )

385
00:19:12,753 --> 00:19:16,257
Menthuthuyoupi
will soon awaken as well.

386
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:22,963
Neferpitou: Meow I get it.
So you’re shaiapouf.

387
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:26,166
Shaiapouf: Well,
a mere observation.

388
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:29,103
Neferpitou: So you can read
my thoughts, can’t you?

389
00:19:29,136 --> 00:19:30,971
I’m not sure I like it.

390
00:19:31,004 --> 00:19:33,640
Shaiapouf: I can understand
the sentiment.

391
00:19:33,674 --> 00:19:34,808
( Chuckles )

392
00:19:35,909 --> 00:19:37,611
Neferpitou: But soon--

393
00:19:37,644 --> 00:19:39,880
( giggles ) He’ll awaken.

394
00:19:39,913 --> 00:19:41,581
That’s wonderful news.

395
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:43,851
’cause, you see,

396
00:19:43,884 --> 00:19:46,120
I still haven’t
made a final decision

397
00:19:46,153 --> 00:19:48,956
about exactly what ability
I should develop.

398
00:19:56,930 --> 00:20:00,200
Oh, yeah! It’s so simple!

399
00:20:00,234 --> 00:20:02,737
All I need to do is fix him.

400
00:20:02,769 --> 00:20:05,572
That’s what i’m
gonna make my ability.

401
00:20:09,243 --> 00:20:12,012
Then i’ll be able
to once again experience

402
00:20:12,045 --> 00:20:14,814
that dreamlike moment with you.

403
00:20:18,719 --> 00:20:20,721
( Laughing )

404
00:20:26,293 --> 00:20:27,828
( Boys groan )

405
00:20:27,861 --> 00:20:30,831
( Panting )

406
00:20:30,864 --> 00:20:32,833
Bisky: Come on!
What are you doing?

407
00:20:32,866 --> 00:20:36,103
At this rate, you’re never going
to defeat knuckle and shoot,

408
00:20:36,136 --> 00:20:37,971
much less the chimera ants!

409
00:20:38,005 --> 00:20:41,976
Are you giving up
on going to the ngl?

410
00:20:42,009 --> 00:20:43,944
( Gon groaning )

411
00:20:43,977 --> 00:20:46,146
No way.

412
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:48,616
We’ll never give up!

413
00:20:48,649 --> 00:20:50,784
We will go back to the ngl!

414
00:20:50,817 --> 00:20:52,986
I don’t care what we have to do!

415
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,022
( Both yelling )

416
00:20:59,026 --> 00:21:00,794
( Palm gasps )

417
00:21:00,828 --> 00:21:04,131
Gon: We’re going back
to save kite.

418
00:21:04,164 --> 00:21:06,733
( Palm groans )

419
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,939
Narrator: After reuniting
with biscuit,

420
00:21:11,972 --> 00:21:14,575
gon and killua
are back to training.

421
00:21:14,608 --> 00:21:19,947
They have but one goal, to get
strong enough to rescue kite.

422
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:24,751
That motivation is pushing gon
to his absolute limits.

423
00:21:25,752 --> 00:21:26,720
♪

424
00:21:26,753 --> 00:21:28,755
( Singing in Japanese )

